name: Offbeat Odyssey Bookseries
description:
Book jackets designed conceptually to connect three unlikely books together. Dan Brown's Angels and Demons, Steven Hall's The Raw Shark Texts, and Hunter Thompson's Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas. All books follow a protagonist who is on a journey in search of something, tangible or not, and who with each book have an increasingly estranged state of mind. 

Am currently trying to find matching sizes for the books to get the perfect fit.

name: Ed Hopper Original
description:
A pop culture take on Edward Hopper's famous "The Lighthouse at Two Lights" done with acrylic paint on canvas.

2x3 ft dimensions.

Available as a print of the original piece, a matted print, or as the actual piece, with only one available and signed by Ryan Claybaugh.

name: Trecena - A Unique Calendar
description:
A calendar design where each month is a different circle that you can turn individually to line up the current date with the pointer extending from the middle. The month is identified by name and numeric form on each circle, and Sunday's are marked a different color for each month. 

Made out of different materials depending on size, right now only a 6" diameter size is available. Also available in only one color scheme at the moment, more are to be added soon!

Each made individually, custom orders can be taken for a price increase.
